    • Method Detail

      • additionalCustomerAccountRelationships

        java.util.Set<Account> additionalCustomerAccountRelationships(Account account)
        PCAccountTransfer already finds related accounts. There might be other account relationships the customer has defined, and the related accounts should be returned.

        Accounts are related if:
        • A policy has been moved from one account to another.
        • An account has been merged to another account.
        • A cancellation has been re-written to another account.
        • A policy has been split or spinned to another account.
        • Accounts have been linked together through the AccountAccount entity.
        Parameters:
        account - the sourceAccount to find all related accounts
        Returns:
        Set of accounts that are related to the account

      • maxAllowedNumberOfAccountsToBeFrozen

        int maxAllowedNumberOfAccountsToBeFrozen(Account account)
        This method is called during the freezing of an account. If the total number of accounts exceed the number that is returned, then the freezing of the account will not happen.
        Parameters:
        account - to see what is the max related accounts to freeze together.
        Returns:
        an int for max allowable accounts to be frozen together.

      • contactRelatedEntityTypesToCopy

        java.util.Set<IEntityType> contactRelatedEntityTypesToCopy()
        PCAccountTransfer will include entities related to Contact based on the set of entity types provided by this method in order to create a copy of these entities in the target shard. These entities are not purged in the source shard after transfer. If the customer has defined their own Contact entities of type AddressBookLinkable/AddressBookConvertable and/or related entities then those types should also be added to the set. Not adding a type to this set would mean that the entity already exists on the target shard and therefore, it won't get copied and created.
        A Contact entity is related if:
        • It is either an AddressBookLinkable or AddressBookConvertable type.
        • It has a FK to either AddressBookLinkable or AddressBookConvertable type.
        • It contains an array of either AddressBookLinkable or AddressBookConvertable type.
        Returns:
        Set of entity types that are related to Contact in order to create a copy of these entities in the target shard.
